<topic xml:id="openscap-packages-installing"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Installing &openscap; and the &ssg;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="souvik.sarkar@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        Install the core packages required to scan and remediate &productname; with &openscap; and the
        &ssg;.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <section xml:id="openscap-packages-installing-core">
    <title>Installing the core packages</title>
    <para>
      To install the required packages, proceed as follows:
    </para>
    <procedure>
      <step>
        <para>
          Install the following packages:
        </para>
<screen>&prompt.sudo;<command>transactional-update pkg install openscap-utils scap-security-guide</command></screen>
      </step>
      <step>
        <para>
          Reboot the system to switch to the new snapshot:
        </para>
<screen>&prompt.sudo;<command>reboot</command></screen>
      </step>
    </procedure>
    <note>
      <para>
        GUI tools such as SCAP Workbench are not available on &productname;. If you need to create a
        tailoring file to customize a profile, do so on a separate machine and transfer the file to
        the &productname; system. You can then apply it using the <option>--tailoring-file</option> option
        with <command>oscap</command>.
      </para>
    </note>
  </section>
</topic>
